  [1mGPT OSS 120B's Complete Analysis of the terminalcp Project:[22m

  [1mProject Overview â€“ terminalcp[22m

  terminalcp is a Node.js library and CLI that lets AI agents (or any
  program) control interactive command-line tools just like a human would.
  It provides a "Playwright-for-the-terminal" style interface where
  processes are started in a pseudo-TTY, and the agent can send keystrokes,
   read output, and keep sessions alive.

  [1mCore Capabilities[22m

  â€¢ Spawn & control any CLI (debuggers, REPLs, build tools, etc.) in
  real-time.
  â€¢ Two output modes:
  - Terminal mode (stdout) â€“ full rendered screen (good for TUIs,
  debuggers).
  - Stream mode â€“ raw incremental output (good for logs, builds).
  â€¢ Full PTY emulation (colors, cursor movement, special keys) via node-pty
   + headless xterm.js.
  â€¢ Multiple concurrent sessions that persist across client disconnects.
  â€¢ MCP server exposing a single JSON-based tool (terminalcp) for AI-driven
   interaction.
  â€¢ CLI (terminalcp command) that mirrors the MCP functionality (start,
  stop, send input, get output, attach, etc.).
  â€¢ Attachable sessions â€“ users can attach to AI-spawned processes from
  their own terminal (like screen/tmux).

  [1mArchitecture[22m

  1. TerminalManager â€“ core library handling PTY creation, I/O, and
  terminal emulation.
  2. TerminalServer â€“ background process listening on a Unix-socket,
  managing all sessions.
  3. TerminalClient â€“ used by both the MCP server and CLI to talk to the
  server.
  4. User Interfaces â€“ MCP server (for AI agents) and CLI (for humans) both
   use the same underlying API.

  [1mTypical Use-Cases[22m

  â€¢ Debugging (LLDB, GDB, pdb) â€“ step-through code, get backtraces, etc.
  â€¢ Running other AI tools (Claude Code, Gemini CLI) as subprocesses.
  â€¢ Driving REPLs, database shells, system monitors.
  â€¢ Testing/automating TUIs (vim, htop) via programmatic API.
  â€¢ Monitoring long-running processes (build logs, server output) with
  incremental streaming.

  [1mHow to Use[22m

  â€¢ MCP: send JSON actions (start, stdin, stdout, stream, stop, etc.) to
  the terminalcp tool.
  â€¢ CLI: terminalcp start  "", terminalcp stdin  "cmd" ::Enter, terminalcp
  stdout , terminalcp attach , etc.
  â€¢ Programmatic: import TerminalManager in TypeScript/JavaScript and use
  its methods (start, sendInput, stdout, stream, stop).

  [1mDevelopment[22m

  â€¢ Install with Node 20+, run npm install, npm test, npm run build.
  â€¢ The server persists sessions in ~/.terminalcp/server.socket.
  â€¢ Sessions can be listed, stopped, or killed via the MCP or CLI.

  [1mIn short:[22m terminalcp provides a robust, programmatic way for AI agents
  (or any code) to spawn, control, and monitor interactive terminal
  applications, with full PTY support, persistence, and both MCP and CLI
  interfaces.
